  "text": "In this section, we extend the dynamic scaling theory outlined in Sec. III to systems subject to dissipative interactions with the environment, so that the time dependence of the density matrix ρ is described by the Lindblad master equation [CITATION_1] . Namely, we assume that the quantum evolution arising from the KZ protocol occurs in the presence of dissipation with the effective coupling u > 0, thus being ruled by Eq. (4). The resulting dynamic KZ scaling framework will provide a unique framework to discuss the interplay between (critical) coherent and dissipative drivings.",
